  "chunk_index": 53,
  "summary": "Kougetsu Joushou confronts Daya=Hana=Anna-Stasia, revealing her true identity as a Russian princess of the Romanov bloodline. He explains that she murdered the composer Medvedev because he was aware of her existence. Driven by a desire to hide her assimilation into Japanese culture and to prevent her lineage from being viewed as \"degenerate,\" she planned a massacre of the Kuragin family. This plan was triggered by economic liberalization reforms that threatened to resurface Medvedev's work, \"Imakagami,\" and expose her secret.\n\nKougetsu further reveals that he is the biological grandson of Anna-Stasia and the twin brother of the deceased McArthur (Ryuujin Raijou). He explains that his mother, Tomiko Akiyoshi, was a twin who secretly gave birth to him to protect his identity. To prove this lineage, Kougetsu presents a gold cross and a talisman left by his mother. He clarifies that his intention in marrying Yuzu—Medvedev's great-granddaughter—is motivated by love rather than a desire for the Higuchi family fortune, despite having the legal standing to claim the inheritance himself.\n\nIn a final psychological attack, Kougetsu labels Anna-Stasia a \"failure\" and a \"puppet\" rather than a god or monarch, accusing her of being a disgrace to the Romanov name. He tells her not to resist him, as doing so would bring shame to her descendants. After delivering this revenge for his mother's death, Kougetsu leaves the location, predicting that the broken Anna-Stasia will likely take her own life rather than lose her remaining dignity.",
